Without prejudice to the provisions of section 31(5) and (6), the Advisory Committee must determine the application for a Geothermal Resources Concession  based on the documents submitted by the applicants, which must include information in respect of—
* description of proposed development;
* cost and schedule for development;
* technical approach and methodology;
* capabilities and track record in use of geothermal
* compliance with health and safety standards; and
* proposed tariff agreements.
